cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with generating 3D models from 2D images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus is on understanding how an object class can articulate and deform, which involves learning a model from annotated images, a task that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of 3D printing, which is related to computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
